Temperature Sensor: A digital temperature sensor is provided using a Microchip TCN75A 2-Wire Serial Temperature Sensor. 
The temperature sensor, IC2, is an I2C device, and is located in the lower right corner of the board. 
 
The TCN75A is rated for an accuracy of +/-1ºC and has selectable resolution from 0.5ºC down to 0.0625ºC. 

The seven bit device address is ‘1001000’. 
 
Digilent provides a library for accessing the temperature sensor. 
This library is available on the Digilent web site and in the third party library repository on github. 
 
The TCN75A provides an alert output that can be programmed for various functions
